IRAN\r\nLAMPIRAN I UNDANG-UNDANG REPUBLIK INDONESIA NOMOR9 TAHUN 1985 TENTANG PERIKANAN\r\nLAMPIRAN II UNDANG-UNDANG REPUBLIK INDONESIA NOMOR 31 TAHUN 2004 TENTANG PERIKANAN\r\nLAMPIRAN III UNDANG-UNDANG REPUBLIK INDONESIA NOMOR 45 TAHUN 2009 TENTANG PERUBAHAN ATAS UNDANG-UNDANG REPUBLIK INDONESIA NOMOR 3 TAHUN 2004 TENTANG PERIKANAN\r\n* * * * * *\r\n\r\n', NULL),
(333, 'English For Agrarian Affairs (HVS)', 6, '152;', 'I/2002', '979-414-863-6', '2002-05-30', 108, 16200, 'Buku berjudul Eglish for Agrarian Affair berisi dua hal utama : a). tata Bahasa (Grammer) dan b) Reading tax. tata bahasa itu dimaksudkan untuk mengulas ulang pokok-pokok tata bahasa sebagai dsar pemahaman teks contoh-contoh kalimat dalam tata bahasa diusahakan dan sebagaian besar memang menggunakan istilah agrarian. hal ini dimaksudkan menonjolkan nuansa-nuansa keagrarian dalam bahasa inggris reading texts yang penulis ambil dari berbagai sumber dimaksudkan untuk menambah nuansa keagrarian dalam bentuk bacaan dan bukan hanya kalimat sebagaimana dalam tata bahasa dari bidang pengukuran misalnya terdapat judul tentang konsep skala "The Concept of Scale" dan dari bidang maanjemen terdapat texs berjudul "land Information" dan dari sisi hukum pertahanan terdapat judul "Feudalism and Tanure" dan sebagainya.\r\n', 'GRAMER\r\nTo Be\r\nTence Review\r\nKelompok Nomina\r\nCiri-ciri Adjetiva, Nomina dan Adverbia\r\nPassive Voice\r\nConcord/Agreement\r\nSentences\r\nREADING TAXS\r\nLand Economics,\r\nLand Information\r\nThe Concepts of Scale\r\nFeudalism and Tanure\r\nIntroducation to Modern Cartography\r\nInstrumen Adjustmens\r\n*introduction\r\nLand Acquisition\r\nThe Fee Tail\r\n*history and general nature \r\nThe Dutch Scool of Cartography\r\n*the dutch scool of cartography\r\n', NULL),
(334, 'The Internet : Issues of Jurisdiction and Controversies Surrounding Domain Names', 2, '153;', 'I/2002', '979-414-868-7', '2002-05-29', 84, 12600, '-', 'THE INTERNET AND TERRITORIALITY\r\nTransborder Legal Implication of Global Network\r\nPrivate International law In Transnational Cyberspace\r\nWich Law Applies\r\nbrusseels and lugano conventions\r\n*the basic rule\r\n*provesional measures\r\n*lis pandens related actions\r\n*actions in tort, dilict and quasi delich\r\n*Exclisive jurisdition in proceedings concerned with registrationof validity\r\n*the draft convention in internatiomal jurisdition and the effecs of foreign judgments in civil and commercial matters : the hague conference on private international law \r\npossible solution\r\n*unifyng the choce of law rules\r\n*unifyng a substtantive law of the internet\r\n*internet as a new jurisdiction\r\nTHE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN DOMAIN NAMES ADN INTELLEKTUAL PROPERTY\r\nThe Domain Names\r\nThe Interface Between The Domain Name System And Trademerk\r\nFAMAUS AND WELL-KNOWN TRADEMERKS\r\nWhen In a Merks Well-Known\r\nThe Distinction Between Famous\r\nFamous and Well-Known Marks in Cyberspece\r\nLEGAL ISSUES\r\nCatagorising disputes\r\n*cyber-squatting or abusive registration\r\n*competing legitimate claims\r\nCauses of Action and Their Difficutien\r\nPRACTICES DESINGED TO MINIMISE CONFLICS ARISING OUT OF DOMAIN NAME REGISTRATIONS RECOMMENDED BY WIPO A CRITICAL EVALUATION\r\nBest Practices for Registration Authoroties\r\nAdministrative Procedure Concerning Abusive Domain Name Registration\r\n*potential for intimidation\r\n*the nature of available judicial review\r\n*smorgasboard approach to law\r\n*relied on potentially unenforcebale contracts\r\nExclusions for Famous and Well-Know Marks\r\nNew GTLDS   \r\n', NULL),
